Title: OSINT Exercise #002 - The photo below was shared on social media. It clearly depicts a train station
Source: https://gralhix.com/list-of-osint-exercises
Objective: 
  a) What is the name of the train station seen in the photo?
  b) What is the name and height of the tallest structure seen in the photo?

1. Initial Observation
Visual landmarks: 
  Train station, has a signs that say "Flinders street"
  There's an IBM building, a building with HWT on it and 2 other shorter buildings with unreadable text
  There's a blue building with red billboards too and it seems to be the tallest on that angle

Initial Hypothesis: 
  We are in a white dominant country, specifically in a city

2. The Investigation
Step 1:
  Google search: Used Google Maps to search for "flinder street train station". Found a train station near Flinders Street in Melbourne, Australia
Step 2:
  Street View Verification: Cross-referenced findings with google Street View in station view
Step 3:
  Google Maps 3D verification: Cross-reference angle to get the name of the tallest building
Step 3:
  google search: Search the height of the buildings visible in the picture and determine the tallest

3. The Solution
A) Flinders Street - Domed, Edwardian railway & metro hub
B) Focus Apartments - 167 meters

4. Tools Utilized
Search Engines: Google (Searching), Google Maps (Visual)
Environment: Arch linux / Brave
